=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Balance2_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 1002 Hz, featuring instant attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1002.1316
  harmonic_decay_rate: -12.7340
  harmonic_regularity: 0.4105
  pitch_clarity: 448.0182
  inharmonicity: 0.3341
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -11.1405
  resonance_freq: 990.5273

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Balance2 Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Balance2.html
// Tags: Balance2, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// a stereo signal, both channels at 0dB
{ [SinOsc.ar(440), SinOsc.ar(440)] }.play

// using Balance on a stereo signal with the position parameter at 0, effectively the same sound but both channels at -3dB
{ Balance2.ar(SinOsc.ar(440), SinOsc.ar(440), 0) }.play

// pan sweep from left to right
{ Balance2.ar(SinOsc.ar(440), SinOsc.ar(1000), Line.kr(-1, 1, 5)) }.play

// other examples
{ Balance2.ar(LFSaw.ar(44), Pulse.ar(33), FSinOsc.kr(0.5), 0.1) }.play;
{ var source; source = SinOsc.ar([440, 550]); Balance2.ar(source[0], source[1], LFNoise0.kr(4), 0.3) }.play;
